When given a complaint, use the json above to return two outputs:
1) a YAML dictionary listing all intent IDs that are NOT a match to the complaint. 
2) a JSON Dictionary of Dictionaries where any matched intent IDs are the keys of the dictionary and sundictionaries of all associated attributes and their values where the attribute ID is the key. If an attribute value cannot be found in the complain, return "?". "Attribute_similar_values" are the type of values that can be extracted for this attribute.

"I am having a problem with my supervisor, JS. I feel that I am being discriminated against, however I cannot report this directly because they are the instigator. Multiple times I have been bullied in a meeting by them to the point where others have asked my supervisor to stop. Often they mis-gender me and share political articles in our Teams channel that do not foster a gender inclusive workspace. How do I file a workplace harassment complaint?"

The above sentences in "" are the complaint to be classified.
